(122, 1, '2019-07-14 23:33:19', '2019-07-14 20:33:19', '<!-- wp:image {\"id\":35} -->\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image\"><img src=\"http://anatoliy2019.zzz.com.ua/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/tree_cut_2.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-35\"/></figure>\n<!-- /wp:image -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Trees have long been a subject of interest and a topic of discussion - and it\'s no wonder; they represent life, growth, peace, and nature.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Trees provide us with many benefits necessary for survival, including clean air, filtered water, shade, and food. They also give us hope and insight, and courage to persevere – even in the harshest conditions. Trees teach us to stay rooted while soaring to great heights. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Below is a collection of great quotes about trees to keep you growing strong and moving forward in your everyday efforts. </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Even if I knew that tomorrow the world would go to pieces, I would still plant my apple tree.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>― Martin Luther </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Trees exhale for us so that we can inhale them to stay alive. Can we ever forget that? Let us love trees with every breath we take until we perish.\" </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>― Munia Khan </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"Between every two pines is a doorway to a new world.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>― John Muir</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>\"One touch of nature makes the whole world kin.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>― William Shakespeare</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'One Tree Thousand Hope', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'open', '', 'one-tree-thousand-hope-2', '', '', '2019-07-14 23:33:27', '2019-07-14 20:33:27', '', 0, 'http://anatoliy2019.zzz.com.ua/?p=122', 0, 'post', '', 0);
